						<summary>

						<p>Pillar set up at the entrance into the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Vēṇugōpalasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription can be assigned to 16th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Built in and begining lost. Seems to renew the grant of lands and grant of further land as a <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya śrōtriyam</hi> to one Kaṁkajiyya.</p>						

						</summary>
